  "title": "MoCap Tools",
  "description": "A tool to quickly bulk-modify animations and facilitate a fast animation-implementation workflow.",
  "longDescription": "<p>Check out my <a href=\"https://youtu.be/UTQyQ3FH9Os\" rel=\"nofollow\">PROMOTIONAL VIDEO</a>, and take a look at the <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1OVx8H7VGQ1_XdaPFxRNlVYDktbdolx7KWTXBbxJLyac/edit?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">documentation</a>.</p><p><br /></p><p>Join my <a href=\"https://discord.gg/se24X9c2Dc\" rel=\"nofollow\">Discord</a> for early access to updates and access to direct support.</p><p><br /></p><p>The <u>M</u>o<u>C</u>ap <u>T</u>ools (MCT) plugin is designed with the express purpose of accelerating the animation-implementation workflow for character locomotion, particularly during the prototyping phase. Rather than needing to go back and forth between Unreal and animation software (Maya, Cascadeur, Blender, etc.), my plugin allows users to trim animations, modify the root bone of animations, generate root-motion curves, blend animation ends, and constrain IK bones — all within the Unreal editor.</p>",
